CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 22, 1955, pg. 1, reads: "Dr. Emile C. Nash...assistant VA medical chief." Portion of accompanying article by George E. Barbour reads: "...The medical scientist is Dr. Emile C. Nash, an assistant chief of the department of gastro-enteroloy (diseases of the digestive tract), who, together with Dr. John Webber, now is interviewing patients, studying X-ray negatives and case histories and treating or directing cures for some sixty ex-servicemen suffering from stomach disorders..."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Emile Nash seated before unlit light boxes with x-rays, in Veterans Administration Hospital, Oakland
